Serves 4-6Ingredients:60ml (1/4 cup) oil2.5ml (1/2 tsp) fenugreek seeds2.5ml (1/2 tsp) black mustard seeds5ml (1 tsp) cumin seeds3-5 curry leaves10ml (2 tsp) garlic paste1 onion, chopped30ml (2 tbsp) fish masala1 large tomato, finely chopped15ml (1 tbsp) tamarind pulp, combined with 375ml (1 cups) waterPinch of salt250ml (1 cup) fenugreek leaves, plus extra for garnishing15ml (1 tbsp) sugar2 garlic cloves, peeled600g salmon fillet, or other sustainable firm-fleshed line fish, portionedAsha's Spice Box: A glossary of exotic Indian ingredientsMethod:1) Heat oil in a pan and fry the fenugreek seeds, mustard seeds and cumin seeds until they start to pop. Add curry leaves, garlic paste and onion and fry until onion begins to turn golden.2) Add masala and tomato and cook for 5 minutes. Add tamarind water and salt and cook until sauce is thickened.3) Stir in fenugreek leaves, sugar, and garlic cloves. Arrange the sliced fish on the sauce in a single layer, cover pan with a lid and cook for 10-15 minutes.4) Sprinkle with fenugreek leaves and serve with rice.